  "text": "The response to H3-that migrant husbands and wives are less likely to be employed-is thus strongly gendered. H3 is confirmed for migrant wives but not for migrant husbands. The employment gap between migrant wives and UK-born/raised South-Asian wives is significantly larger among Pakistani Muslims than among Indian Sikhs (see Online Table A6 ). This is in line with H5 and supports the interpretation of the employment gap as being at least partly explained by gender norms, but may also be influenced by gendered forms of discrimination against Muslim women [CITATION_1] .",
